  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Resident Technical Officer M&E",
  "description": "<p>Responsibility</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Correspondence with Consultant’s and client’s representatives</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with regulatory and statutory requirements Attending meetings (Consultant, Progress, Technical coordination and other Meeting)</li>\n  <li>Submission of shop drawing &amp; materials for approval within the stipulated program</li>\n  <li>Managing consultants and clients expectations so as to control within project budget</li>\n  <li>Supervision of sub-con to ensure works are carried out according to Work Method Statement Coordinating and monitoring sub-con work schedules according to the master and detailed work programmes</li>\n  <li>Conducting inspections work performance by sub-contractors</li>\n  <li>Conducting inspections and verification of delivered MEP materials</li>\n  <li>Ensuring that updated drawings are used by all for construction</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper document control in support of Project Manager and Quantity surveyor's submission of contractual claims</li>\n  <li>Coordinating with the relevant trades such as Architectural and Structural and to work out the coordination drawing</li>\n  <li>Assist in value engineering and proposal for the various submissions</li>\n  <li>Submission of progress report</li>\n  <li>Supervising the works of Construction Coordinators</li>\n  <li>Project handover e.g. maintenance schedule, as built drawings, manuals, catalogue</li>\n  <li>Assist in Tender Preparation</li>\n  <li>Coordinating the arrangement of the testing and commissioning of M&amp;E systems including the handover of all replacements parts, warranties, operating manuals and maintenance tools and equipment.</li>\n  <li>Submission of MEP report to client</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirement</strong></p>\n<p>· Degree in Mechanical &amp; Electrical Engineering (recognized by PEB)</p>\n<p>· Min 5 years work experience in construction industry</p>\n<p>· Have solid background in MEP (technical competence)</p>\n<p>· Knowledgeable in local building regulation</p>\n<p>· Knowledgeable in software such as AutoCad and BIM</p>\n<p>· Excellent Co-ordination skill</p>\n<p>· Good Interpersonal Skills</p>\n<p>· Good Problem solving skill</p>",
